cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it introduces a new learnable module that allows for spatial manipulation of data within the network, resulting in state-of-the-art performance on several benchmarks. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it introduces a new module that can be inserted into existing convolutional architectures, giving neural networks the ability to actively spatially transform feature maps without any extra training supervision or modification to the optimization process. Additionally, it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it introduces a differentiable module that can be used to improve the performance of neural networks. Finally, it may belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves the manipulation of data within a network.
